#: ../source/repair.rst:7
# ff5a21f1072044eeb9bc4e0a46ed40a0
msgid "For photos and step-by-step instructions on repairing your XO or putting replacement parts in, go to http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Repair."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:9
# 620504c2b37c46138af2a263a84d5336
msgid "Refer to http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Repair_center_locations to get to the most recent directory of repair centers, if you do not want to repair your XO yourself."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:12
# 0dc2b544623c4f71ad74f804b18bb5e1
msgid "Recalibrating the touchpad on the XO 1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:14
# 79dbcb8e07064a198f9207abd207217b
msgid "If the pointer is not following your finger on the touchpad of a XO 1.0, or if it jumps to the corners when you touch the touchpad, please try this recalibration procedure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:16
# a4dfd7a3614a4f78a6d9c480133e7eaf
msgid "Hold down the three keys at one time: the upper left, upper right, and lower right of the keyboard and the fourth key, fn, the lower leftmost key, as the last one pressed, and then release them all."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:20
# 0bce60b0189f46efaa65b5b45c8243b5
msgid "If this doesn't help, try shutting down the laptop and removing the battery for ten seconds before restarting."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:22
# 9d786603fbfe4290a5c411bd295cda00
msgid "Finally, plug a standard USB mouse into your laptop to bypass the problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:25
# 10178969fe854dd9872899900669919c
msgid "How to do a Keyboard Test"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:27
# a885768e4c74408d94bfa4b7f77455ce
msgid "Checking for keys that stay down or appear stuck"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:29
# 39cbcccc16f6431f97e84861041aad4b
msgid "Your XO must have a developer's key to do this keyboard test. Refer to http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Developer_key for more information about developer's keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:31
# 76bcedecd5a547a3a5924e30ec006386
msgid "With the XO off, hold down the \"check mark\" game button (above the power button) while pushing the power button. After start up, the screen displays \"Release the game keys to continue\" and shows a text diagram of which key is pressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:32
# 644e1dda9e204d4bb2f663f8e7f6da1c
msgid "Release the \"check mark\" game button."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:33
# b391e2fc5a17439792985db2726adf1f
msgid "Next, after you see \"Type the Esc key to interrupt automatic startup,\" press the escape key in the upper left hand corner of the keyboard layout (a circle with an x). The XO displays an ok prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:34
# 0fe1cf55c7fc4894bbb636c255d59d24
msgid "At the ok prompt, type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:36
# 7f1ed761f045420ab01aec41d15e3443
msgid "``test keyboard``"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:38
# c80357ea6c1d4ea8a01fe823c1b8dc1d
msgid "and press enter."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:40
# 2f2e17ed462f4a4584091dadd11a452f
msgid "A blue keyboard map displays on the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:42
# ca168ee0b3764c18a9eef5fcfcc0bb0f
msgid "Press keys one at a time to see the keyboard map turn the key light blue."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:43
# da0d180bac104603acf98a7ab3e2d2c3
msgid "If the display on screen shows a light blue key constantly, the keyboard has a problem with that particular key sticking. Refer to a repair center for full diagnosis and repair at http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Repair_center_locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:44
# e9bcf73b2d4b4b05ab4a74a16fb2ce51
msgid "Press the the escape key (circle with an x) again to exit the keyboard test."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:45
# c28e299be0ea4f69b2cb4c377dcbb6dd
msgid "At the ok prompt, type reboot to restart."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:48
# df651bd849f5471586edc59830952ca3
msgid "Repairing damage to the keyboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:50
# d0094e8021ce4158a761a0ca6f848679
msgid "If your keyboard becomes damaged, normally it has to be replaced. Replacements are available through the repair centers. Information on spare parts and repair centers can be found at http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Repair_center_locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:53
# 41dabc4ce8014838af08abd45dcf9172
msgid "Troubleshooting the internal XO hardware"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:55
# 174387ada1924c119103151be5e79078
msgid "The XO can give you information about possible repairs that are needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:57
# 0b6f3c3773134ad49014db68f4d7882e
msgid "Start by pressing the power button for a second, and then answer the following questions. Does the Power LED half-circle light up?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:59
# 12fc9aabc356480496c785b6013b8f26
msgid "When the power button is pressed once, and the power LED doesn't turn on, first try resetting it."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:61
# 39c717913b5b4b50b366712051385536
msgid "To reset the XO, remove all power sources from the laptop:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:63
# 44e2b3c638ee4357b87e6041bf8e5082
msgid "Take the battery out and remove the power adapter."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:64
# 275c37ed89b8414983aecb0a93101a56
msgid "Wait two minutes. This allows embedded hardware to lose all power and reset itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:65
# 4a7a440e4b7a4b55a040210ac52a26f6
msgid "Replace at least one source of power, either the battery or power adapter, and watch the power/battery LED while you do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:67
# 9cd053df63e0410cb081cedc7e41ec85
msgid "The battery LED should flash orange momentarily (about a quarter of a second) when power is first reapplied. If you do not see this flash, you either have a motherboard hardware problem or faulty EC firmware installed. Contact a repair center for assistance."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:69
# 3dc051940bc24d37b0384f7b048d21b3
msgid "If the power LED doesn't turn on or flash, but the laptop proceeds to illuminate the backlight and even start, the problem may be either the LEDs themselves or the power LED driver. The LEDs are in series, so if one fails they may both fail to light."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:71
# eb610d145601455dab583edf441e57b7
msgid "On rare occasions, the power button becomes stuck mechanically. In this case, the laptop does not detect the depression of the power button, and does not turn on. Ensure that the power button is moving freely by pressing it a few times."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:73
# 9802547b0b76494c847e86bf22fe9d25
msgid "If the battery LED flashed on restoration of power and the power button isn't stuck, and no other signs of life are detected, then you can't determine the reason for failure. Contact a repair center for assistance. Does the display light up?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:75
# dd898e676bea4437afea674905262099
msgid "After starting the XO and viewing the power LED, the next visible feedback from the XO is that the display lights up. The LCD display should be initialized with white, then begin to show text or graphics. The backlight for the screen should be turned on, even if the backlight was previously turned off."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:77
# 2289ed642ec04826a068fe10548e782f
msgid "If this does not happen then the boot sequence may not be operating correctly. Next, look at the Microphone activity LED to see if it is lit. If the power LED and the microphone LED are both lit then a serious boot error has occurred and you should contact a repair center for assistance. Can you hear the startup sound when the XO starts?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:79
# 5f0ea9ebe5ef434d8e3fe1ca43ceac9f
msgid "If the startup sound does not play, this usually indicates a problem that a repair center needs to fix. Yes, the startup sound plays"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:81
# c020a855517547a390465b45e10e3e25
msgid "If the display doesn't initialize, but the boot sound plays, then this is probably a problem with the display. No, the XO boots normally, but no boot sound plays"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:83
# 798b707e942f4d288421f1b35976b278
msgid "If no boot sound is played, but the machine boots normally and has audio, it is possible that the default boot volume to has been changed to 0. While the boot sound is playing, you can adjust the volume using the volume adjust keys. This modified volume setting is saved and used for future boots. Try increasing the volume right after starting the laptop a few times, and see if the boot sound returns."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:85
# b4a988f6619a4f85995c12b0d07c065f
msgid "If no boot sound is played, and the machine boots normally but has no audio see http://wiki.laptop.org/go/XO_Troubleshooting_AV. Does the display remains blank after starting up?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:87
# 3c06feb6d92e422cbced660da61339d8
msgid "Sometimes the display is active (including backlight), but no text or graphics appear. This problem can be caused by removing the power to an XO while it is upgrading the firmware. You should contact a repair center for assistance. Does the display say \"Connect power to proceed\"? Sometimes a firmware update requires two sources of power, both a battery and a power adapter. If this is the problem, provide both sources of power and reboot. The XO should proceed with a firmware update and boot normally. Is the display is showing an XO icon only?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:89
# b65799eda37b4f1492389c4599f97740
msgid "This means that the XO has started the startup process."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:91
# 7747551758b1468fba30722f04ca324e
msgid "You can see much more information about your Open Firmware by holding the \"check mark\" game button (above the power button) after powering on. That makes Open Firmware display more detailed messages about what it is doing during the secure boot process (including early boot messages from the Linux kernel). The messages are in English only. Is it showing an XO icon with a serial number and three icons below it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:93
# c41d6285ec67488db6b68d3ab71edb5a
msgid "If the laptop powers up, but stops when displaying the XO icon in the middle of the screen, followed by a serial number (e.g. CSN74902B22) and three icons (SD disk, USB disk, Network signal strength), it is looking for its activation lease. This should eventually print \"Activation lease not found\" at the top of the screen and power-off soon thereafter."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:95
# 3f5fca6969df4405977721d5fce29051
msgid "The solution is to re-activate the laptop. Obtain a copy of the lease (or a new lease) from your country activation manager, place it (named \"lease.sig\") in the top-level directory of a USB key and boot the laptop. See the \"what to do with activation keys\" section within: http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Activation_and_Developer_Keys. Is it showing an XO icon with a \"sad face\" above it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:97
# 25c6bbfe57a8458c927d3c7e467a3059
msgid "This means that Open Firmware couldn't find a signed operating system on the internal flash memory. Firmware bootup also looks on USB memory sticks and SD cards for signed operating system software."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:99
# 71f6eb9361384a26a6e96b3c3ce4cc05
msgid "Try upgrading or re-installing the software: http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Secure_Upgrade. XO icon with a single dot below it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/repair.rst:101
# d12e0ff1826e4700aed286e49ad937b9
msgid "If the XO powers up, but stops when just displaying the XO icon in the middle, with a single dot below it, it means that something was wrong when the Linux operating system started. When this happens, try upgrading or reinstalling the XO. If this has happened to the same XO more than one time, consider a repair center for full diagnosis and repair at http://wiki.laptop.org/go/Repair_center_locations."
msgstr ""

